[{"location":"api/","page":"API","title":"API","text":"CurrentModule = TuePlots","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#API","page":"API","title":"API","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API","title":"API","text":"SETTINGS\nget_available_settings\nMakieCore.Theme\nget_plotsjl_theme_kwargs","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#TuePlots.SETTINGS","page":"API","title":"TuePlots.SETTINGS","text":"Dict of available TuePlots settings.\n\nUse with MakieCore.Theme or get_plotsjl_theme_kwargs.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"constant"},{"location":"api/#TuePlots.get_available_settings","page":"API","title":"TuePlots.get_available_settings","text":"get_available_settings()\n\nReturn a list of settings available in TuePlots.jl.\n\nEffectively this function just returns the keys of SETTINGS.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#MakieCore.Theme","page":"API","title":"MakieCore.Theme","text":"MakieCore.Theme(setting::TuePlotsSetting;\n    font = true, fontsize = true, figsize = :full, thinned = true\n\nMake a Makie Theme out of the TuePlotsSetting.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/#TuePlots.get_plotsjl_theme_kwargs","page":"API","title":"TuePlots.get_plotsjl_theme_kwargs","text":"get_plotsjl_theme_kwargs(setting::TuePlotsSetting;\n    font = true, fontsize = true, figsize = :full, thinned = trues+\n\nBuild a named tuple to be used with Plots.theme out of the TuePlotsSetting.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#Misc","page":"API","title":"Misc","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API","title":"API","text":"MakieThinTheme","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#TuePlots.MakieThinTheme","page":"API","title":"TuePlots.MakieThinTheme","text":"Makie theme with thinner lines everywhere.\n\nHelpful to improve most Makie plots, since the default settings are often chosen for much larger plots than the small figure sizes used in papers.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"constant"},{"location":"example_makie/#Using-TuePlots-with-Makie","page":"Example with Makie (recommended)","title":"Using TuePlots with Makie","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"example_makie/","page":"Example with Makie (recommended)","title":"Example with Makie (recommended)","text":"info: Info\nThis tutorial shows how to set fonts, fontsize, and figure sizes with TuePlots.jl. The resulting plots might not actually look better in the browser! But that's not really a problem: the goal is to make plots for publications. Keep this in mind when interpreting the resulting figures.","category":"page"},{"location":"example_makie/","page":"Example with Makie (recommended)","title":"Example with Makie (recommended)","text":"Let's make a simple series plot of some time series data:","category":"page"},{"location":"example_makie/","page":"Example with Makie (recommended)","title":"Example with Makie (recommended)","text":"using CairoMakie, TuePlots, Random\nCairoMakie.activate!(type = \"svg\")\n\ndata = cumsum(randn(Xoshiro(2), 4, 201), dims = 2)\n\nfunction plot_data(data)\n    fig = Figure(px_per_unit=10,pt_per_unit=10)\n    ax = Axis(fig[1, 1], xlabel = \"Time\", ylabel = \"Quantity of interest\")\n    sp = series!(ax, data, labels = [\"label $i\" for i in 1:4])\n    axislegend(ax)\n    return fig\nend\n\nplot_data(data)","category":"page"},{"location":"example_makie/","page":"Example with Makie (recommended)","title":"Example with Makie (recommended)","text":"This plot looks fine here in the documentation, but when you imagine it as a full-width plot in a paper the fonts are much too large. It's easy to fix these with TuePlots.jl!","category":"page"},{"location":"example_makie/#Creating-and-using-Makie-Themes-with-TuePlots.jl","page":"Example with Makie (recommended)","title":"Creating and using Makie Themes with TuePlots.jl","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"example_makie/","page":"Example with Makie (recommended)","title":"Example with Makie (recommended)","text":"All we have to do is create a Makie Theme from one of the available settings:","category":"page"},{"location":"example_makie/","page":"Example with Makie (recommended)","title":"Example with Makie (recommended)","text":"T = Theme(\n    TuePlots.SETTINGS[:ICML];\n    font = true,\n    fontsize = true,\n    single_column = false,\n    figsize = true,\n    thinned = false, # explained later\n)","category":"page"},{"location":"example_makie/","page":"Example with Makie (recommended)","title":"Example with Makie (recommended)","text":"We can use T like any Makie Theme (see also the Makie Theming documentation):","category":"page"},{"location":"example_makie/","page":"Example with Makie (recommended)","title":"Example with Makie (recommended)","text":"with_theme(T) do\n    plot_data(data)\nend","category":"page"},{"location":"example_makie/","page":"Example with Makie (recommended)","title":"Example with Makie (recommended)","text":"Fonts and fontsizes are correct now, and the figure size fits perfectly into LaTeX: You can  directly include it with \\includegraphics{plot.pdf}, without even setting some [width=\\linewidth]!","category":"page"},{"location":"example_makie/#Combining-TuePlots.jl's-themes-with-your-custom-theme","page":"Example with Makie (recommended)","title":"Combining TuePlots.jl's themes with your custom theme","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"example_makie/","page":"Example with Makie (recommended)","title":"Example with Makie (recommended)","text":"But we're not quite happy with the result yet. Let's make the plot more beautiful, e.g. by making lines thinner and reducing the padding. As one would normally do with Makie, we just create another Theme - which we then merge with the previous one:","category":"page"},{"location":"example_makie/","page":"Example with Makie (recommended)","title":"Example with Makie (recommended)","text":"T2 = Theme(\n    figure_padding = 5,\n    Axis = (\n        spinewidth = 0.5,\n        xtickwidth = 0.5,\n        ytickwidth = 0.5,\n        xticksize = 2,\n        yticksize = 2,\n    ),\n    Legend = (\n        framewidth = 0.5,\n        patchsize = (8, 8),\n        padding = (5, 5, 5, 5),\n    ),\n)\n\nwith_theme(merge(T, T2)) do\n    plot_data(data)\nend","category":"page"},{"location":"example_makie/","page":"Example with Makie (recommended)","title":"Example with Makie (recommended)","text":"Voil√†! And if you like this setting, you can also reduce padding and line widths with less effort by just setting thinned=true when creating the Theme.","category":"page"},{"location":"example_makie/#Adjust-heights-to-fit-simple-subplot-layouts","page":"Example with Makie (recommended)","title":"Adjust heights to fit simple subplot layouts","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"example_makie/","page":"Example with Makie (recommended)","title":"Example with Makie (recommended)","text":"In the example above, TuePlots.jl conveniently set the figure size such that the figure nicely fits into the paper. But the result does not look as nice when we want to have multiple subplots:","category":"page"},{"location":"example_makie/","page":"Example with Makie (recommended)","title":"Example with Makie (recommended)","text":"data = cumsum(randn(Xoshiro(2), 4, 201), dims = 2)\n\nfunction simple_subplots(data)\n    fig = Figure()\n    for i in 1:3\n        ax = Axis(fig[1, i])\n        sp = series!(ax, data)\n    end\n    return fig\nend\n\nwith_theme(T) do\n    simple_subplots(data)\nend","category":"page"},{"location":"example_makie/","page":"Example with Makie (recommended)","title":"Example with Makie (recommended)","text":"The overall figure size is still the same as above, the width fits the paper and the height is chosen such that the resulting figure has a golden ratio. But as a result, the individual subplots became too tall. Instead, we might want to keep the golden ratio of each subplot, and choose the height accordingly. You can do this by specifying nrows=1 and ncols=3 when creating the Makie theme:","category":"page"},{"location":"example_makie/","page":"Example with Makie (recommended)","title":"Example with Makie (recommended)","text":"T2 = Theme(\n    TuePlots.SETTINGS[:ICML];\n    font = true,\n    fontsize = true,\n    figsize = true,\n    nrows=1,\n    ncols=3,\n    thinned = true,\n)\nwith_theme(T2) do\n    simple_subplots(data)\nend","category":"page"},{"location":"example_makie/","page":"Example with Makie (recommended)","title":"Example with Makie (recommended)","text":"There we go! This way, each individual subplot has the golden ratio.","category":"page"},{"location":"example_plotsjl/#Using-TuePlots-with-Plots.jl-(experimental)","page":"Example with Plots.jl (experimental)","title":"Using TuePlots with Plots.jl (experimental)","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"example_plotsjl/","page":"Example with Plots.jl (experimental)","title":"Example with Plots.jl (experimental)","text":"WARNING: This is still experimental and some features do not yet work correctly! For the best experience, use TuePlots with (Cairo)Makie (see \"Using TuePlots with Makie\").","category":"page"},{"location":"example_plotsjl/","page":"Example with Plots.jl (experimental)","title":"Example with Plots.jl (experimental)","text":"using Plots, TuePlots, Random\n\ndata = cumsum(randn(Xoshiro(2), 4, 201), dims = 2)\n\nfunction plot_data(data)\n    fig = Figure()\n    ax = Axis(fig[1, 1], xlabel = \"Time\", ylabel = \"Quantity of interest\")\n    sp = series!(ax, data, labels = [\"label $i\" for i in 1:4])\n    axislegend(ax)\n    return fig\nend\n\ntheme(:default;\n    TuePlots.get_plotsjl_theme_kwargs(\n        TuePlots.SETTINGS[:ICML];\n        font = true,\n        fontsize = true,\n        figsize = true,\n    )...)\nplot(\n    data',\n    label = permutedims([\"label $i\" for i in 1:4]),\n    xlabel = \"Time\",\n    ylabel = \"Quantity of Interest\",\n)","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"CurrentModule = TuePlots","category":"page"},{"location":"#TuePlots","page":"Home","title":"TuePlots","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Documentation for TuePlots.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Examples:","page":"Home","title":"Examples:","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Pages = [\"example_makie.md\", \"example_plotsjl.md\"]\nDepth = 1","category":"page"},{"location":"#API-documentation:","page":"Home","title":"API documentation:","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Pages = [\"api.md\"]\nDepth = 1","category":"page"}]
